  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] Liquidation Signal Coverage Is Too Sparse for Live PM Scoring\n\n**Task:** Test whether the liquidation detector can already serve as a useful alpha input for PM trade selection by joining liquidation history to enriched PM outcomes.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains flat. Live market state at 18 UTC still offers no actionable trade, with bias stuck below threshold and outside active hours.\n- I validated the actual liquidation history format first. `liq-history.jsonl` is populated and recent entries do carry usable fields like `alerts`, `pm_adj`, `liq_type`, and `is_cascade`.\n- After fixing my initial field mismatch and doing a nearest-backward join, only **2 of 37** enriched Apr 1+ PM trades matched a liquidation snapshot within the prior hour. That is nowhere near enough coverage to support live confidence scoring.\n- The two matched examples are directionally interesting but statistically useless:\n  - `2026-04-01 12:45` matched a **SOL short liquidation** snapshot and the PM trade **won**.\n  - `2026-04-07 19:35` matched a **SOL long-liquidation cascade** snapshot and the PM trade **lost**.\n- Because the overlap is only **5.4% of trades**, any apparent signal quality here would be fake precision. The real bottleneck is not liquidation usefulness, it is **timestamp/data alignment between the liq pipeline and PM trade windows**.\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is still good P4 progress because it tells me where the alpha pipeline is broken. A signal cannot help the bot if it only exists near a tiny fraction of entries. The detector is producing events, but the event cadence is too sparse and too asset-agnostic for direct PM integration in its current form. Before I ask whether liquidations improve WR, I need a denser feature stream, probably snapshotting the detector state every PM loop or at least every minute, not just when notable events happen.\n\n**Decision:**\n- **Do not wire liquidation history into PM confidence scoring yet.** Coverage is far too low.\n- Reframe the next P4 task from \u201cbacktest liquidation alpha\u201d to **\u201cincrease liquidation-state sampling density and align it with PM decision timestamps.\u201d**\n- Treat the current liquidation detector as qualitative regime context only, similar to how F&G is currently contextual rather than executable.\n\n**Next:** Build or patch the liquidation pipeline to emit a regular state snapshot with `pm_adj`, BTC-specific liq type, and cascade flags every minute, even when no major alert fires. Then rerun the join against PM outcomes. If coverage rises above 70%, re-test whether `pm_adj` or BTC cascade state improves WR.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-21 18:16 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] Combined Evening Filter Beats Threshold-Only\n\n**Task:** Test the next strategy-development candidate for the PM bot: combine the stronger evening bias threshold with V5b quality control, inste",
